<h2>Instructions for Developers</h2>
<p>Welcome to the Comserv Application Documentation. Here are some guidelines and best practices to keep in mind while working with this project:</p>
<ul>
    <li><strong>Naming Conventions:</strong> Follow the existing naming conventions for consistency. If you encounter any deviations, normalize them to maintain uniformity.</li>
    <li><strong>Code Quality:</strong> Ensure that all code is well-documented and adheres to the project's coding standards. Use meaningful variable and function names to enhance readability and maintainability.</li>
    <li><strong>Error Handling:</strong> Implement robust error handling in all subroutines to ensure the application behaves predictably under unexpected conditions.</li>
    <li><strong>To-Do List:</strong> If you identify any issues or potential improvements in the code, add them to the 'Todo' section of this documentation.</li>
    <li><strong>Code Reviews:</strong> Submit your code for review by peers to catch potential issues early and ensure adherence to best practices.</li>
</ul>

<h2>Current Issue: Error Handling and Logging</h2>
<p>We have been working on improving the error handling and logging in the `Root.pm` controller. The main issues were:</p>
<ul>
    <li>Insufficient detail in error messages.</li>
    <li>Difficulty in tracing errors due to lack of line numbers and subroutine names.</li>
</ul>

<h3>Successes</h3>
<ul>
    <li>Added line numbers and subroutine names to error messages.</li>
    <li>Improved the `error.tt` template to display detailed error messages and stack traces.</li>
</ul>

<h3>Failures</h3>
<ul>
    <li>Some error messages are still not detailed enough.</li>
    <li>Need to ensure all error messages include the file name, line number, and subroutine name.</li>
</ul>

<h3>To-Do</h3>
<ul>
    <li>Review all error messages in `Root.pm` to ensure they include the file name, line number, and subroutine name.</li>
    <li>Test the application to ensure the new error handling and logging are working as expected.</li>
    <li>Update the documentation to reflect any further changes made.</li>
</ul>

<p>We are committed to evolving the Comserv application to meet the needs of our users. Please contribute by keeping this documentation up to date and following the guidelines provided.</p>

